<%#
  Magic-link welcome modal — opened via
  $store.modals.open('magic-link-welcome', { message, next }).
  Rendered inside studio/_modal_host through its own <template x-if>, which
  provides backdrop, card chrome, scroll lock, escape, click-outside and the
  mount animation.

  Celebration handoff after a consumed magic link (MagicLinksController#consume,
  both the new-signup and returning-sign-in paths). The user just landed on the
  contest they came from; this modal shows a brief "You're in!" beat, then the
  cta_redirect block drains for ~2.5s and transfers to the entry-tokens upsell
  (props.next). The user can click the CTA to go there immediately — it's a real
  link to props.next, so a click navigates now instead of waiting out the drain.

  Auto-opened from the server flash[:magic_link_welcome] via the inline script in
  layouts/application.html.erb (mirrors the email-change-pending auto-open on
  /account, but at layout level so it fires on whichever contest page the link
  returned to).

  Single root element wrapping the template (the host mounts this partial through
  its own template x-if; multiple sibling roots there silently no-op). The x-data
  props reader is defined inline — no importmap factory.
%>
<div x-data="{ get props() { return ($store.modals.current() || {}).props || {} } }">
  <%= render 'modals/blocks/card_header',
        size:        :lg,
        icon_emoji:  '🎉',
        title:       "Welcome to Turf Totals" do %>
    <span x-text="props.message || 'You\'re in! Your 6 picks are saved.'"></span>
  <% end %>

  <%# Drains for ~2.5s then transfers to props.next (entry tokens). The CTA is a
      real link to props.next, so clicking it navigates immediately. props.next
      is server-controlled (tokens_buy_path), never user input. %>
  <%= render 'modals/blocks/cta_redirect',
        href_key:         "props.next",
        label_html:       "Get entry tokens &rarr;",
        duration_seconds: 2.5 %>
</div>
